Count 1 - Operate under influence (5th) - No contest plea.  Convicted.  State moves to dismiss and read in count 2, Operate with PAC over .02 and count 3, Operate after revocation.  Motion granted.  Sentence is withheld.  Defendant is placed on probation to DOC for three (3) years.  Conditions of probation are:
1) Twelve (12) months jail, under the Huber Law; Six (6) months to commence immediately and six (6) months stayed to be imposed at agent's discretion;
2) Pay $750.00 fine x 3, plus costs, total of $3,860.50;
3) Ignition interlock for period of revocation;
4) AODA assessment and follow through counseling with driver safety plan;
5) Pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC.  
In addition, defendant's operating privileges are revocation for a period of thirty-six (36) months.  
Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights. 
Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief. 
Ineligible Voting Notice & Acknowledgment.  
